<div id="main_content">
	<h2>UCF's First Plug-In Hybrid Car Saves Energy, Gas (With Video)</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By Christine Dellert
		
		<span class="date">Nov. 15, 2007</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="http://news.ucf.edu/resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/1000/NE1237/en_US/car crop.jpg" height="" width=""  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: Jacque Brund</p>
			
			<p>The plug-in hybrid Toyota Prius was converted with 20 extra batteries and a rewired internal computer. </p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=00240041045494c8d01161d3164c1007c79">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
							
								<h3>Story Images</h3>
								<ul id="story_images">
							
						<li>
						<a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=00240041045494c8d01161d3164c1007c79&amp;img_mode=1&amp;index=0">
							<img width="100" alt="Article Main Picture" src="http://news.ucf.edu/resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/1000/NE1237/en_US/car plug full.jpg"  />
						</a>
						</li>
						
						
					
			
					
						
						
							
						<li>
